Cherished Memories

A Life of Purpose and Love

Alva Johnson was a radiant spirit whose presence lit up every room. With a quick wit, infectious laughter, and a disarming smile, she exuded a playful charm. Her eyes always twinkled with mischief and love, reflecting her warmth and boundless energy.

Coming from a long line of strong, fearless Jamaican women who forged their own paths across North America, Alva followed in their footsteps with grace and determination. She earned her BS from Nazareth College in Michigan, where she was both a talented athlete and assistant basketball coach.

Her professional journey led her to become President of a prominent insurance agency in Buffalo, where she was both a respected business leader and trusted friend. But Alva's true passion lay in uplifting others and serving her community.

For more than forty years, she called Buffalo home, dedicating countless hours to making her city better. Whether leading the Boards of Directors for United Way and the Buffalo Urban League, or serving on various community councils, Alva's heart and mind were always focused on making the world around her better.

🎓 Education & Athletics

BS from Nazareth College, talented basketball player and assistant coach

💼 Professional Excellence

President of prominent Buffalo insurance agency, respected business leader

❤️ Community Service

Board leader for United Way, Buffalo Urban League, and Environmental Management Council

🏈 Buffalo Pride

Passionate Bills fan who loved sharing Buffalo's rich history

🎵 Jazz Enthusiast

Deep love for jazz music that matched her vibrant spirit

🌟 Legacy of Love

Making everyone feel special, valued, and like they belonged

The web of our life is of a mingled yarn, good and ill together.
— William Shakespeare

Her Enduring Legacy

What truly defined Alva was her compassion for people, her unwavering commitment to community, and her unshakable belief in the power of connection. She had a remarkable way of making everyone feel special—like they mattered, like they belonged.

Through her love, laughter, and community work, Alva created a legacy that will continue to uplift us all. Her spirit will forever remain with those who loved and cherished her.
❀ ❀ ❀

Forever in Our Hearts

Deeply missed by her sister Joan, sister-in-law, nieces, grandnephew, cousins, extended family, and countless dear friends whose lives she touched with her boundless love and energy.

Daughter of Doris and Jasper Johnson • Sister of Johnnie, Marcia, and Joan
